{% faqAccordion
   title="Summer Staff FAQ"
   titleAlign="center"
   allowMultiple=true %}
{% faqItem
   question="Why should I work at camp?"
   answer="The community you'll build during your time at Camp Otyokwah will lead to lifelong relationships, the skills you gain will boost your resume and prepare you for your future career, and your time at camp will deepen your faith and allow you to rely on the Lord at a whole different level."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="How old do I have to be to work at camp?"
   answer="Counselors, recreation leaders, worship leaders, LIT counselors, photographers, and videographers must be at least 18 years old. Lifeguards and craft leaders must be at least 16 years old."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="Do I get paid to work at camp?"
   answer="Pay starts at $200 per week for high school students and $350 per week for college-age students, with returning staff receiving increased pay. All meals, lodging, and recreational activities are included in the compensation package. Some colleges offer matching grants applied to tuition."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="What if I can't work at camp all summer long?"
   answer="Certain positions at Camp Otyokwah require that you are present for the full summer, while others have the flexibility to work with your summer needs. We're willing to work with individual schedules."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="What if I need an internship?"
   answer="Camp Otyokwah can help fulfill internship requirements for various positions that support career development."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="As a counselor, what does leading a Bible Study look like?"
   answer="Counselors lead daily Bible study within their cabin groups, focusing on building relationships with campers and challenging them to grow in their faith in Christ."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="When does camp start and end?"
   answer="Staff training begins in early June, and camp concludes for staff in late July."
   category="summer-staff" /%}

{% faqItem
   question="When are applications due?"
   answer="Applications are due by May 1. Early submissions are encouraged."
   category="summer-staff" /%}
{% /faqAccordion %}

